  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various strategies, including:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Regulations\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Establishing reporting thresholds for large cash transactions\n\n2. Investigative Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Tracing financial transactions\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Using digital forensics and data analytics\n\n3. International Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations across jurisdictions\n\n4. Legal Prosecution\n- Criminal charges for money laundering\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n5. Technological Solutions\n- Advanced transaction monitoring systems\n- AI and machine learning for detecting suspicious patterns\n- Blockchain tracking technologies\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities through comprehensive legal and technological frameworks.",
